      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix and bake, 28 to 30 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 180°C fan. Butter and line two round tins. Whisk together the {{plain-flour}}, {{cocoa-powder}}, {{caster-sugar}}, {{bicarbonate-of-soda}}, and {{sea-salt-fine}}. In a separate bowl, whisk the {{eggs}}, {{rapeseed-oil}}, {{buttermilk}}, and the {{vanilla-extract}} for the sponge. Pour the wet ingredients into the dry and whisk to a smooth batter, this is the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "velvet crumb",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp9yubr900001gv4cxvg5xxz"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " in the making. Divide evenly between the two tins. Bake for 28 to 30 minutes until a skewer comes out clean. Cool in the tins for 10 minutes, then turn out onto a rack.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the frosting",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the {{cream-cheese}} and {{unsalted-butter}} together until smooth. Add the sifted {{icing-sugar}} and the {{vanilla-extract}} for the frosting and beat until thick and spreadable. Refrigerate for 15 minutes if it is too soft to hold its shape.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Assemble",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Place one sponge on a plate. Spread one third of the frosting over the top. Place the second sponge on top and spread the remaining frosting over the top and sides. Refrigerate for 30 minutes to set before serving.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
